22-acre offshore island located in outer Penobscot Bay; 23 miles southeast of Rockland; Knox; Co. Steep sea cliffs and boulder fields dominate the northern; eastern and southern boundaries of the island; while the west side slopes from the high point to an inter-tidal zone with rock and pebble beaches
